==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Pour
<hw>Pour</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Poured</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pouring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>pouren</ets>, of
uncertain origin; cf. W. <ets>bwrw</ets> to cast, throw, shed, <ets>bwrw
gwlaw</ets> to rain.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cause to flow in a
stream, as a liquid or anything flowing like a liquid, either out of a
vessel or into it; <as>as, to <ex>pour</ex> water from a pail; to
<ex>pour</ex> wine into a decanter; to <ex>pour</ex> oil upon the
waters; to <ex>pour</ex> out sand or dust.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To send forth as in a stream or a flood; to emit; to
let escape freely or wholly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I . . . have <qex>poured</qex> out my soul before the Lord.</q>
<rj><qau>1 Sam. i. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now will I shortly <qex>pour</qex> out my fury upon thee.</q>
<rj><qau>Ezek. vii. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>London doth <qex>pour</qex> out her citizens !</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wherefore did Nature <qex>pour</qex> her bounties forth⟦br⟧
With such a full and unwithdrawing hand ?</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To send forth from, as in a stream; to discharge
uninterruptedly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Is it for thee the linnet <qex>pours</qex> his throat ?</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pour</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Pour
<hw>Pour</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To flow, pass, or issue in a
stream, or as a stream; to fall continuously and abundantly; <as>as, the
rain <ex>pours</ex>; the people <ex>poured</ex> out of the
theater.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the rude throng <qex>pour</qex> on with furious pace.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pour</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Pour
<hw>Pour</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A stream, or something like a stream;
a flood.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>pour</xex> of
rain.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Miss Ferrier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poureliche</ent>⟦br⟧
